Package org.tms.api

TMS is a framework for ad-hoc analysis of complex data.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    BaseElement
    This interface is the base from which all other TMS Table System interfaces extend.
    Cell
    A Table cell.
    Column
    A Table column, containing a vertical slice of cells.
    IndexableTableElements
    This interface defines the methods that are common to TableContext and Table instances that allow Row, Column, Cell, and Subset, labels to be indexed.
    InitializableTableProperties
    This interface defines the methods that are common to TableContext and Table instances, each of which have several TablePropertys that can be initialized automatically from a template instance when creating new TableContexts and Tables.
    Row
    A Table row, containing a horizontal slice of cells.
    Subset
    A Table subset, containing a collection of rows, columns, cells and other subsets.
    Table
    A standard two dimensional table consisting of Rows, Columns, and Cells, and, optionally, Subsets.
    TableContext
    A collection of Tables, initializable TablePropertys, and optional thread pools.
    TableElement
    TableRowColumnElement  
    Taggable
    Methods that allow TableElements to be selectively tagged.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Access
    This enum defines the methods available to access Row, Column, Subset, and Cell table elements from their parent containers.
    ElementType
    The core elements provided in the TMS system
    TableProperty  

Package org.tms.api Description

TMS is a framework for ad-hoc analysis of complex data. This package contains the core apis to create, manage, and manipulate TMS Tables.
Since:
"1.0"
Version:
"1.1"
